  "body": {
    "export_view": {
      "value": "<p>A Return Merchandise Authorization (RMA) is a part of the Reverse Logistics cycle, where a defective product is returned to the manufacturer or vendor during the product's warranty period. This allows the vendor to diagnose and correct the issue with the product, and proceed with a refund or replacement for defective products or reject the claim if the product was damaged or broken by misuse or improper installation. Ultimately, the decisions are made at the supplier's discretion to credit these items.</p><p>RepairQ offers tools for your staff to mark defective items as Pending RMA status and to send batches of items to the supplier for approval. Once you receive a decision on the replacement of these items, you are able to update the inventory status of those items, to maintain accurate inventory records.</p><a class=\"external-link\" data-card-appearance=\"embed\" data-layout=\"center\" data-original-height=\"480.00\" data-original-width=\"853.34\" data-width=\"100.00\" href=\"https://youtu.be/V0gKRpAtrIQ\" rel=\"nofollow\">https://youtu.be/V0gKRpAtrIQ</a><span class=\"confluence-embedded-file-wrapper image-center-wrapper\"><img class=\"confluence-embedded-image image-center\" src=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/download/attachments/1932525631/Control%20-%20f79824.png?api=v2\"></span><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932460163/RMA+Process+Initiate+an+RMA+From+a+Ticket\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932460163\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Initiate an RMA From a Ticket</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1931116776/RMA+Process+Initiate+an+RMA+Through+Inventory+Fulfillment\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1931116776\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Initiate an RMA Through Inventory Fulfillment</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932296378/RMA+Process+Sending+RMA+Items+to+the+Supplier+RMA+Batch\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932296378\" data-linked-resource-version=\"6\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Sending RMA Items to Supplier</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932591235/RMA+Process+Reconcile+an+RMA\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932591235\" data-linked-resource-version=\"7\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Reconcile an RMA</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1932198033/RMA+Process+Transferring+RMAs+to+a+Central+Location+for+Processing\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1932198033\" data-linked-resource-version=\"4\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">RMA Process: Transferring RMAs to a Central Location for Processing</a></p><p><a href=\"https://servicecentral.atlassian.net/wiki/spaces/SCD/pages/1934721039/Reports+Inventory+Usage\" data-linked-resource-id=\"1934721039\" data-linked-resource-version=\"5\" data-linked-resource-type=\"page\">Reports: Inventory Usage</a> - Detail Reporting for RMA Credit/RMA Rejected/Shrinkage</p><p /><p /><p>START 1.20.X</p>",
